Cell["\<\
I have devised several schemes for constructing unbiased hexagonal walks. I \
present here a scheme that allows of modification so as accommodate \
site-specific weights:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.535565923228661*^9, 3.535566045894064*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
We place the origin at a red node, and assume that the walker begins his walk \
at that node (so his first step is necessarily a red step).\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5355640474170094`*^9, 3.5355640668801928`*^9}, {
  3.5355641067550983`*^9, 3.5355641490885773`*^9}}],

